MSP430Timer32khzMapC presents as paramaterized interfaces all of the 32khz hardware timers on the MSP430 that are available for compile time allocation by "new Alarm32khz16C()", "new AlarmMilli32C()", and so on.
Platforms based on the MSP430 are * encouraged to copy in and override this file, presenting only the * hardware timers that are available for allocation on that platform.
@author Cory Sharp <cssharp@eecs.berkeley.edu> @version $Revision: 1.5 $ $Date: 2010-06-29 22:07:55 $

Msp430Alarm is a generic component that wraps the MSP430 HPL timers and
compares into a TinyOS Alarm.

@author Cory Sharp <cssharp@eecs.berkeley.edu>
@see  Please refer to TEP 102 for more information about this component and its
         intended use.

